article.description: James Madison pulls away late; beats Delaware 88-82
article.headline: James Madison pulls away late; beats Delaware 88-82
article.linkText: James Madison pulls away late; beats Delaware 88-82
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Jackson Kent made five 3-pointers and finished with a career-high 19 points to help James Madison beat Delaware 88-82 on Wednesday. James Madison led by just one point, 78-77, with two minutes left, but made 8 of 8 free throws in the final 34 second to seal it. Tom Vodanovich had 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds for James Madison (13-9, 6-3 Colonial Athletic Association). Yohanny Dalembert added 17 points and Ron Curry had 15 points, seven rebounds and eight assists. James Madison trailed 34-30 with 3:35 left in the first half, but Kent made back-to-back 3-pointers during a 10-0 run for a 40-34 lead at the break. Kent had 14 points at halftime. Marvin King-Davis was 10 of 17 from the field and 11 of 13 from the line to total a career-best 31 points for Delaware (4-16, 3-6). Chivarsky Corbett and Devonne Pinkard had 12 points apiece.
